<refnamediv>
<refname>Compiling Gegl</refname>
<refpurpose>
How to compile Gegl 
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
  <refsect1 id="overview">
    <title>Compiling Gegl on UNIX-like systems</title>
    <para>
      After you've run <filename>configure</filename>, you then run the
      <command>make</command> command to build the package.
<programlisting>
$ make
</programlisting>
    </para>
    <para>
      This will build the main <filename>libgegl</filename> library in gegl
      subdirectory. Then it will make the <filename>libtestsuite</filename>
      library in the <filename>tools/testsuite</filename> subdirectory. This
      is the simple unit testing framework that Gegl uses.  
      After that the unit tests in the <filename>test</filename> directory 
      are compiled and run. Finally if --enable-gtk-docs was passed to configure 
      the gtk-docs for gegl will be built in the 
      <filename>docs/reference/gegl/html</filename> directory.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>

